Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameTuple4DReadOnly

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFrameQuaternionBasics, FixedFrameTuple4DBasics, FixedFrameVector4DBasics, FrameQuaternionBasics, FrameQuaternionReadOnly, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameVector4DBasics, FrameVector4DReadOnly
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameQuaternion, FrameVector4D
    public interface FrameTuple4DReadOnly
extends us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder
    Read-only interface for a 4D tuple expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Tuple4DReadOnly, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameTuple4DReadOnly. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on tuples occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameTuple4DReadOnly extends Tuple4DReadOnly, it is compatible with methods only requiring Tuple4DReadOnly. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameTuple4DReadOnly.

    • Method Detail

      • dot

        default double dot​(FrameTuple4DReadOnly other)
        Calculates and returns the value of the dot product of this tuple with other.

        For instance, the dot product of two tuples p and q is defined as:
        p . q = ∑i=1:4(pi * qi)

        Parameters:
        other - the other vector used for the dot product. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the value of the dot product.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.

      • epsilonEquals

        default boolean epsilonEquals​(FrameTuple4DReadOnly other,
                              double epsilon)
        Tests on a per component basis if this tuple is equal to the given other to an epsilon.

        If the two tuples have different frames, this method returns false.

        Parameters:
        other - the other tuple to compare against this. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use when comparing each component.
        Returns:
        true if the two tuples are equal and are expressed in the same reference frame, false otherwise.

      • equals

        default boolean equals​(FrameTuple4DReadOnly other)
        Tests on a per component basis, if this tuple is exactly equal to other.

        If the two tuples have different frames, this method returns false.

        Parameters:
        other - the other tuple to compare against this. Not modified.
        Returns:
        true if the two tuples are exactly equal component-wise and are expressed in the same reference frame, false otherwise.
